listitem.para:
password: this is a password encrypted by a one-way
	  function (crypt), relying on DES,
	  MD5, SHA-256 or
	  SHA-512. The special value
	  “x” indicates that the encrypted password
	  is stored in /etc/shadow;

gid: unique number for the user's main
	  group (Debian creates a specific group for each user by
	  default);

login directory, assigned to the user for storage of their
	  personal files (the environment variable $HOME
	  generally points here);

password (optional): This is only used to join a group when
	  one is not a usual member (with the newgrp or
	  sg commands, see sidebar);
